<br>
I have had my share of ups and downs, both with Sons of Tao, and now with Pax.  One thing I have seen entirely too many times since starting this game, is people leaving perfectly good guilds for the sake of further personal development.  I COMPLETELY understand the reasoning of those who leave for this reason, if they are among the few who have actively participated and sacrificed their goals for the sake of the guild, as I know Thork and Ember have.  They only want to be able to pursue things they have put off to help the guild.  Although I don't agree that leaving is the solution, I completely understand and respect their decision.<br>
<br>
For those who choose to leave ONLY because they aren't getting what they want, or because they want more but don't want to help the guild in the process....I say they never should have joined a guild in the first place (that's not directed at anyone that left, just my personal feelings on those kinds of people).<br>
<br>
So....now that there are no leaves left on the bush from my beating around it, :O here is the solution I propose:<br>
<br>
All guilds should recognize and welcome the needs of all level groups.  Every guild should have an officer, or small group of officers, responsible for recruiting/helping/leveling/raiding with members of all level groups.  That would help the guild cater to the high end game, and give the lower level characters something to look forward to.  Very often, we focus so much on guild's &quot;average level&quot; group that we turn off those on either side of that average....if that makes sense.<br>
<br>
My proposition to secure the future of Pax, then, is this:  Give each officer a level group that he/she is responsible for.  Make sure that officer is willing to recruit, counsel, plan and attend raids with, etc. his/her assigned level group.  Yes, it will mean taking time away from your personal pursuits, but if you are an officer in a guild, that should have been an understood requirement from the beginning.<br>
<br>
AND....if you get tired of doing the job, or need some time off to pursue your own interests...DON'T LEAVE!!!  Talk to the guild leader and other officers.  Tell them you need a break, and get someone else to cover for you, so you don't abandon those who look to you for support and guidance.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'm off my soapbox now.  I'm all for having a high end raiding guild, but let's not forget where we all started, and those times in our early adulthood that we really had to struggle to find a pickup group, becasue no one in the guild was available to help.  Just a thought.  What do you guys think?<br>
<br>
*NOTE - The preceding comments are not directed at anyone who left recently, as there are no high end characters to help with the things they are pursuing.  These comments are mine, and mine alone, and do not reflect the feelings of the Pax Familla guild.  If you are offended by anything I said, then it must apply to you and.....it hurts, don't it?<br>
<br>
All Hail Pax Familla<br>
